 {"id":"bd-1dm","title":"Add tracing integration for rich output debugging","description":"## Purpose
Integrate tracing (structured logging) throughout the rich output system to enable detailed debugging and diagnostics when output issues occur.

## Why This Matters
When rich output has issues (wrong mode detected, colors not showing, formatting broken), we need detailed logs to diagnose:
1. What mode was detected and why
2. What environment variables were seen
3. What terminal capabilities were detected
4. What rendering decisions were made

Without logging, debugging output issues is guesswork.

## Implementation

### 1. Add Tracing to OutputDispatcher
```rust
impl OutputDispatcher {
    pub fn new() -> Self {
        let is_tty = std::io::stdout().is_terminal();
        let json_flag = /* from args */;
        let env_vars = Self::collect_relevant_env();

        tracing::debug!(
            is_tty = is_tty,
            json_flag = json_flag,
            "Initializing OutputDispatcher"
        );

        let mode = Self::detect_mode(is_tty, json_flag, &env_vars);
        tracing::info!(mode = ?mode, "Output mode determined");

        let color_depth = Self::detect_color_depth(&env_vars);
        tracing::debug!(color_depth = ?color_depth, "Color depth detected");

        Self { mode, color_depth, ... }
    }

    fn collect_relevant_env() -> HashMap<String, String> {
        let vars = ["TERM", "COLORTERM", "NO_COLOR", "FORCE_COLOR", 
                    "CI", "GITHUB_ACTIONS", "CLAUDE_CODE", "CODEX_CLI"];
        let mut env = HashMap::new();
        for var in vars {
            if let Ok(val) = std::env::var(var) {
                tracing::trace!(var = var, value = %val, "Environment variable");
                env.insert(var.to_string(), val);
            }
        }
        env
    }

    fn detect_mode(is_tty: bool, json_flag: bool, env: &HashMap<String, String>) -> OutputMode {
        // Log each decision point
        if json_flag {
            tracing::debug!("JSON flag set, forcing Machine mode");
            return OutputMode::Machine;
        }

        if env.contains_key("CLAUDE_CODE") {
            tracing::debug!("CLAUDE_CODE env detected, forcing Machine mode");
            return OutputMode::Machine;
        }

        if env.contains_key("CODEX_CLI") {
            tracing::debug!("CODEX_CLI env detected, forcing Machine mode");
            return OutputMode::Machine;
        }

        if env.get("CI").map(|v| v == "true").unwrap_or(false) {
            tracing::debug!("CI=true detected, forcing Machine mode");
            return OutputMode::Machine;
        }

        if !is_tty {
            tracing::debug!("Not a TTY, using Machine mode");
            return OutputMode::Machine;
        }

        tracing::debug!("TTY detected with no overrides, using Human mode");
        OutputMode::Human
    }
}
```

### 2. Add Tracing to Rendering
```rust
impl OutputDispatcher {
    pub fn print_rich(&self, markup: &str) {
        tracing::trace!(markup = markup, mode = ?self.mode, "print_rich called");

        match self.mode {
            OutputMode::Human => {
                let rendered = self.render_markup(markup);
                tracing::trace!(rendered_len = rendered.len(), "Rendered with ANSI");
                println!("{}", rendered);
            }
            OutputMode::Machine => {
                let plain = strip_markup(markup);
                tracing::trace!(plain_len = plain.len(), "Stripped to plain text");
                println!("{}", plain);
            }
            OutputMode::Quiet => {
                tracing::trace!("Suppressed in quiet mode");
            }
        }
    }

    pub fn print_renderable<R: Render>(&self, renderable: &R) {
        let type_name = std::any::type_name::<R>();
        tracing::debug!(renderable_type = type_name, "Rendering widget");

        let segments = renderable.render(self.terminal_width());
        tracing::trace!(segment_count = segments.len(), "Generated segments");

        // ... render segments
    }
}
```

