### 4. Add Tracing Spans for Commands
```rust
fn cmd_status(output: &OutputDispatcher, ...) -> Result<()> {
    let span = tracing::info_span!("cmd_status");
    let _guard = span.enter();

    tracing::info!("Starting status command");

    // ... command implementation

    tracing::info!("Status command completed");
    Ok(())
}
```

### 5. Log Levels
Define clear log level semantics:
- **ERROR**: Something went wrong with output (panic recovery, I/O error)
- **WARN**: Unexpected but handled (unknown TERM, fallback to ASCII)
- **INFO**: High-level operations (mode detected, command started/finished)
- **DEBUG**: Decision points (why this mode, why this color)
- **TRACE**: Low-level details (every print call, segment counts)

### 6. Structured Fields
Use consistent field names:
```rust
// Good
tracing::debug!(mode = ?mode, is_tty = is_tty, "Detected output mode");

// Bad  
tracing::debug!("mode={:?}, tty={}", mode, is_tty);
```

