## What
Transform the daemon startup output into a tree-style progress display showing each initialization step.

## Current Output (Plain)
```
Starting daemon...
Loading ipset...
Applying iptables rules...
Starting proxy on :12345...
```

## New Output (Rich)
```
───────────────── rust_proxy Daemon ──────────────────────────

Starting rust_proxy daemon...

├ Loading configuration...                          ✓
├ Resolving target domains (127 domains)...         ✓
├ Fetching IP ranges...
│   ├ AWS ranges (4,821 CIDRs)                      ✓
│   ├ Cloudflare ranges (15 CIDRs)                  ✓
│   └ Google ranges (892 CIDRs)                     ✓
├ Creating ipset 'rust_proxy_targets'...            ✓
├ Applying iptables NAT rules...                    ✓
└ Starting transparent proxy on :12345...           ✓

┌─ Daemon Running ────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                             │
│  Proxy:     mesh-us (http://us-wa.proxymesh.com:31280)      │
│  Listen:    127.0.0.1:12345                                 │
│  Targets:   127 domains + 5,728 IP ranges                   │
│  Health:    Checking every 30s                              │
│                                                             │
│  Press Ctrl+C to stop                                       │
│                                                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Why This Design
- Tree structure shows hierarchy (IP ranges are sub-steps)
- Checkmarks appear as each step completes
- Count details (domains, CIDRs) provide visibility
- Final panel summarizes running state
- Ctrl+C hint for stopping

