## What
Create src/output/theme.rs defining rust_proxy's visual identity through a semantic color palette and style presets.

## Why
Consistent colors across all commands create a professional, cohesive experience. Semantic colors (success=green, error=red) reduce cognitive load - users don't have to learn arbitrary color meanings.

## Visual Identity Goals
rust_proxy deals with networking, security, and proxies. The theme should convey:
- Trust & Security: Blues, cyans for networking themes
- Activity & Flow: Cyan for active/primary elements
- Health & Status: Traffic-light semantics (green/yellow/red)
- Professional Polish: Consistent, not garish

## Theme Struct

```rust
pub struct Theme {
    // Status colors (traffic light)
    pub success: Color,      // green - operations succeeded
    pub warning: Color,      // yellow - attention needed
    pub error: Color,        // red - failures
    pub info: Color,         // blue - informational

    // Element colors
    pub primary: Color,      // cyan - headers, active items
    pub secondary: Color,    // bright_blue - secondary accent
    pub muted: Color,        // bright_black (gray) - dim/inactive
    pub highlight: Color,    // bright_white - emphasized values

    // Proxy health colors (match HealthStatus enum)
    pub healthy: Color,      // bright_green
    pub degraded: Color,     // bright_yellow
    pub unhealthy: Color,    // bright_red
    pub unknown: Color,      // bright_black (gray)

    // Data type colors (consistent highlighting)
    pub bytes: Color,        // bright_magenta - byte counts
    pub latency: Color,      // bright_cyan - ping times
    pub timestamp: Color,    // bright_black - dates/times
    pub domain: Color,       // bright_blue - target domains
    pub ip: Color,           // bright_yellow - IP addresses
    pub provider: Color,     // magenta - provider names
}
```

## Style Presets

Create convenience functions:
- styles::header() -> bold + primary color
- styles::subheader() -> secondary color
- styles::label() -> muted color
- styles::value() -> highlight color
- styles::success_msg() -> bold + success color
- styles::error_msg() -> bold + error color
- styles::warning_msg() -> bold + warning color
- styles::info_msg() -> info color

## Global Theme Accessor

```rust
pub fn theme() -> &'static Theme {
    static THEME: std::sync::OnceLock<Theme> = std::sync::OnceLock::new();
    THEME.get_or_init(Theme::default)
}
```

## Color Choices Rationale

| Color | Usage | Why |
|-------|-------|-----|
| cyan | Primary/headers | Evokes networking, tech, trust |
| green | Success/healthy | Universal "good" signal |
| yellow | Warning/degraded | Universal "caution" signal |
| red | Error/unhealthy | Universal "bad" signal |
| bright_black | Muted/inactive | Recedes visually, not distracting |
| magenta | Data values | Stands out without clashing |
| bright_blue | Domains | Tech/URL association |
| bright_yellow | IPs | Distinct from domains |

